    bibo:volume "4013" ;
    dc:creator "Gustafsson, Daniel R.; Bush, Sarah E." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Four new species of Brueelia Kéler, 1936 (Phthiraptera: Ischnocera: Philopteridae) from African songbirds (Passeriformes: Sturnidae and Laniidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241673>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241676>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241677>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241678> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241673>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3 – 4 Brueelia rigbyi n. sp. ex Corvinella melanoleuca. 3, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 4, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241673/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241676>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 12. Male genitalia, dorsal views. 9, Brueelia clara n. sp. 10, Brueelia rigbyi n. sp. 11, Brueelia tkachi n. sp. 12, Brueelia coryliventer n. sp. Abbreviations: lf = lateral fold; mf = median fold." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241677>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 16. Female subgenital plates and vulval margins, ventral views. 13, Brueelia clara n. sp. 14, Brueelia rigbyi n. sp. 15, Brueelia tkachi n. sp. 16, Brueelia coryliventer n. sp. Abbreviations: vms = vulval marginal setae; vos = vulval oblique setae; vss = vulval submarginal setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241677/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241678>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 18. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 17, Brueelia clara n. sp. 18, Brueelia rigbyi n. sp. Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; as 1 – 2 = anterior setae 1 – 2; avs 1 – 3 = anterior ventral setae 1 – 3; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; mds = mandibular seta; mts 1 – 5 = marginal temporal setae 1 – 5; os = ocular seta; pcs = preconal seta; pas = preantennal seta; pos = preocular seta; pts = post-temporal seta; s 1 – 4 sensilla 1 – 4; vsms 1 – 2 = ventral submarginal setae 1 – 2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

